         <div type="translation">
            <p>To the Divine S[pirits]. Arescus[a] (slave) of [-] Severa [lived] [X]
               years [---]. Quartio [---], slave [of] the empero[r], l[ived(?) X ---]</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Line 2: The first deceased’s name was likely in the
               nominative—“Arescusa”—corresponding with the nominative case of the second deceased’s
               name—“Quartio.” The gentilicium of Arescusa’s mistress is likely missing. </p>
            <p>Line 4: It is unclear whether the numeral indicating the number of years the deceased
               lived is complete. It is at least twenty. The rest of the age at death formula
               (months and days? lived) is missing. </p>
            <p>Line 5: It is unclear what is missing. Another title could be missing or perhaps the
               name of the emperor whose slave Quartio was (cf. CIL VIII, 5415).</p>
            <p>Line 7: The rest of the age at death formula (years, months?, and days? lived) is
               missing. </p>
         </div>
